      • PROPERTY_JSON_RAW_VALUE

        public static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_JSON_RAW_VALUE
        Marks a string property to contain JSON data. If set to true, the string value is converted to JSON and included in the JSON export. If this fails, the value is ignored.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • PROPERTY_CONFIG_EMBEDDED

        public static final java.lang.String PROPERTY_CONFIG_EMBEDDED
        Marks a context-aware configuration to be embedded into the main JSON response of the "config" processor. This behavior is enabled by default, you can disabled it by setting it to false. In this case, the main response contains a link to a separate URL of the configuration.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
